NAME
       cop - a generic build system

SYNOPSIS
       cop [COMMAND] …

       Hello

COMMANDS
       help [--man-format=FMT] [OPTION]… [TOPIC]
           display help about cop and cop commands

       init [--repodir=DIR] [OPTION]… 
           make the current directory a repository

       record [OPTION]… [FILE or DIR]…
           create a patch from unrecorded changes

COMMON OPTIONS
       These options are common to all commands.

       --help[=FMT] (default=auto)
           Show this help in format FMT. The value FMT must be one of auto,
           pager, groff or plain. With auto, the format is pager or plain
           whenever the TERM env var is dumb or undefined.

       --version
           Show version information.

MORE HELP
       Use `cop COMMAND --help' for help on a single command.
       Use `cop help patterns' for help on patch matching.
       Use `cop help environment' for help on environment variables.

EXIT STATUS
       cop exits with the following status:

       0   on success.

       123 on indiscriminate errors reported on standard error.

       124 on command line parsing errors.

       125 on unexpected internal errors (bugs).

BUGS
